All features and critical bug fixes should be in for the 1.2.0 release 
by the time you read this (See 
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/releasenotes.html#1_2_0_changes for 
a complete list).  We're using HEAD as the candidate.  Commits are 
frozen while we run our internal test cycle. It usually takes about a 
week to complete (Our coarse test plan outline can be found here: 
http://crawler.archive.org/cgi-bin/wiki.pl?CrawlTestPlan).  Let us know 
if ye come across any bugs that'll kill a crawl.
St.Ack
